rdog.com|publisher=}}</ref>\n**[[Sherdog#Beatdown of the Year|Beatdown of the Year (2008)]] <small>vs. [[Joe Stevenson]] on January 19, 2008</small><ref>[http://www.sherdog.com/news/articles/7/Sherdogs-Miscellaneous-Awards-for-2008-15727 Beatdown of the Year \u2013 Sherdog\u2019s Miscellaneous Awards for 2008]. Sherdog.com. Retrieved on October 30, 2011.</ref>\n\n===Submission grappling===\n*'''[[International Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Federation|IBJJF World Championships]]'''\n**2000 \u2013 [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship#Feather .28Pena.29|Black Belt Pena: 1st Place]]\n**1999 \u2013 [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship#Light .28Leve.29|Brown Belt Leve: 3rd Place]]\n**1998 \u2013 [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship#Feather .28Pena.29|Blue Belt Pena: 2nd Place]]\n**CBJJ Brazilian Team Championships\n**2000 \u2013 Marrom Preta Leve: [[Nova Uni\u00e3o (mixed martial arts)|Nova Uniao]], 1st Place\n*'''Other Credentials'''\n**[[Grapplers Quest]] Lightweight Championship Superfight Winner\n**1997 [[Joe Moreira]] Tournament \u2013 [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Blue belt|Blue belt]], 1st place\n**1999 Copa Pacific Tournament \u2013 Gold medal\n**[[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Black belt|Black belt]] awarded 3 weeks prior to the 2000 World Jiu-Jitsu Championship\n**Believed to have earned the fastest [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Black belt|Black belt]] of all Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu practitioners\n\n===Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu===\n*'''[[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship]]'''\n** [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Jiu-Jitsu Championship Gold Medal]]; [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Black belt|Black belt]] division\n** [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Jiu-Jitsu Championship Silver Medal]]; [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Blue belt|Blue belt]] division\n** [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Jiu-Jitsu Championship Bronze Medal]]; [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Brown belt|Brown belt]] division\n**First American to win gold in the [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Black belt|Black belt]] category\n*'''Awards'''\n**[[Nova Uni\u00e3o (mixed martial arts)|Nova Uni\u00e3o Competition Team]] (Reserved for the four top team competitors)\n**1997 - [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Blue belt|Blue belt]] awarded by [[Ralph Gracie]]\n**2000 - [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu ranking system#Black belt|Black belt]] awarded by [[Andre Pederneiras]]\n\n{{Col-end}}\n<small>1 {{note|1}} Penn unofficially unified the [[UFC Lightweight Championship]] when he defeated [[Sean Sherk]] at [[UFC 84]].<ref name=\"Rabey\"/><ref name=\"Rick\"/><ref name=\"Hernandez\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mmamania.com/2011/10/27/2516764/history-in-the-making-b-j-penn-becomes-the-undisputed-lightweight |title=History in the Making: B.J. Penn becomes the undisputed lightweight king at UFC 84 |publisher=MMA Mania |last=Hernandez |first=Sergio}}</ref></small>\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n| draws= 2\n| nc= \n| ko-wins= 7\n| ko-losses= 4\n| sub-wins= 6\n| sub-losses= 1\n| dec-wins= 3\n| dec-losses= 9\n| dq-wins= \n| dq-losses= \n| other-wins= \n| other-losses= \n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center| 16\u201314\u20132\n|[[Clay Guida]]\n|Decision (unanimous)\n|[[UFC 237]]\n|{{dts|2019|May|11}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n|\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|16\u201313\u20132\n|[[Ryan Hall (grappler)|Ryan Hall]]\n|Submission (heel hook)\n|[[UFC 232]] \n|{{dts|2018|December|29}}\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|2:46\n|[[Inglewood, California]], United States\n|{{small|Return to Lightweight.}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|16\u201312\u20132\n|[[Dennis Siver]]\n|Decision (majority)\n|[[UFC Fight Night: Chiesa vs. Lee]]\n|{{dts|2017|June|25}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Oklahoma City, Oklahoma]], United States\n|\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|16\u201311\u20132\n|[[Yair Rodr\u00edguez]] \n|TKO (front kick and punches) \n|[[UFC Fight Night: Rodr\u00edguez vs. Penn]] \n|{{dts|2017|January|1