{"title_page": "Money in the Bank (2020)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network event}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n<!--{{current sport|sport=pro wrestling|event=professional wrestling PPV}}-->\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name       = Money in the Bank (2020)\n|image      = \n|caption    = \n|tagline    = <!-- DO NOT PUT ANYTHING HERE WITHOUT A REFERENCE INCLUDED TO A WP:RS -->\n|promotion  = [[WWE]]\n|brand      = [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]]<br>[[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]\n|date       = May 10, 2020\n|attendance = <!-- DO NOT PUT ANYTHING HERE WITHOUT A REFERENCE INCLUDED TO A WP:RS -->\n|venue      =WWE Performance Center \n|city       = \n|wwenlast   = [[WrestleMania 36]]\n|wwennext   = \n|event      = [[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Money in the Bank (2019)|2019]]\n|nextevent2 = \n}}\n'''Money in the Bank''' is an upcoming [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] (PPV) and [[WWE Network]] [[List of WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network events|event]], produced by [[WWE]] for their [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brand divisions]]. It is scheduled to take place on May 10, 2020. It will be the eleventh event under the [[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]] chronology.\n\nThe event was originally scheduled to take place at the [[Royal Farms Arena]] in [[Baltimore, Maryland]], but the venue canceled all shows [[impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports|due to the]] [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. WWE has announced changes in plans for the event and now it is going to take place at wwe performance center\n\n== Production ==\n=== Background ===\n[[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]] (MITB) is an annual [[Gimmick (professional wrestling)|gimmick]] pay-per-view produced by [[WWE]] since 2010 and generally held between May and July. The concept of the show comes from WWE's established [[Money in the Bank ladder match]], in which multiple wrestlers use [[Ladder match|ladders]] to retrieve a briefcase hanging above the ring. The briefcase contains a contract that guarantees the winner a match for a world championship of their choosing at any time within the next year. Both the men's and women's matches feature eight wrestlers, evenly divided between the [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brands]]. Male wrestlers compete for a contract to grant them a match for either Raw's [[WWE Championship]] or SmackDown's [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]], while female wrestlers compete for a [[Raw Women's Championship]] or [[SmackDown Women's Championship]] match contract. 2020 will be the eleventh event in the Money in the Bank chronology.<ref name=\"2020event\"/>\n\n====Impact of the coronavirus pandemic====\nThe event was originally announced with [[Baltimore]]'s [[Royal Farms Arena]] as host.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lambert|first=Jeremy|title=WWE Money In The Bank 2020 Scheduled For May 10 In Baltimore, MD|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/wwe-money-bank-2020-scheduled-may-10-baltimore-md|work=Fightful|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"2020event\">{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE MONEY IN THE BANK 2020 DETAILS|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/134349/wwe-money-in-the-bank-2020-details.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> However, [[Maryland]] issued a [[stay at home order]] on March 30, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Barnes|first=Sophia|url=https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/maryland-governor-larry-hogan-latest-monday-march-30-coronavirus-outbreak-covid-19-stay-at-home-order/2258161/|title=Maryland to Enact Stay-at-Home Order Monday as Coronavirus Cases Top 1,400|work=NBC4 Washington|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> Subsequently on April 9, the host venue cancelled the event due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], and began issuing refunds. WWE has yet to announce whether the event will still go on from a different location (such as the [[WWE Performance Center]] in [[Orlando]] where all of their other shows have been held since mid-March).<ref>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE MONEY IN THE BANK WILL NOT TAKE PLACE IN BALTIMORE, ROYAL FARMS ARENA ANNOUNCES CANCELLATION|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/135465/wwe-money-in-the-bank-will-not-take-place-in-baltimore-royal-farms-arena-announces-cancellation.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wilen|first=Jerome|title=WWE Money in the Bank pay-per view canceled due to COVID-19 outbreak|url=https://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/153495-wwe-money-in-the-bank-pay-per-view-canceled-covid-19/|work=WrestleView|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> WWE did air an advertisement promoting Money in the Bank during the second half of [[WrestleMania 36]], but with no references to a specific venue.<ref name=\"WM36Part2\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 results: Powell\u2019s live review of Night Two featuring Brock Lesnar vs. Drew McIntyre for the WWE Championship, John Cena vs. \u201cThe Fiend\u201d Bray Wyatt in a Firefly Funhouse match, Edge vs. Randy Orton in a Last Man Standing match, Rhea Ripley vs. Charlotte Flair for the NXT Women\u2019s Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/05/wrestlemania-36-results-powells-live-review-of-night-two-featuring-brock-lesnar-vs-drew-mcintyre-for-the-wwe-championship-john-cena-vs-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-in-a-firefly-funhouse-match/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Storylines===\nThe show will include matches that result from scripted storylines, where wrestlers portray [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] in scripted events that build tension and culminate in a wrestling match or series of matches. Results are predetermined by WWE's writers on the Raw and SmackDown brands,<ref name=\"HSW\">{{cite web|title=How Pro Wrestling Works|url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|last=Grabianowski|first=Ed|work=HowStuffWorks|publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]|access-date=March 5, 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|archive-date=November 18, 2013|df=}}</ref><ref name=WWEnt>{{cite web|title=Live & Televised Entertainment|url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|publisher=WWE|access-date=March 21, 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5esskNFVE?url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|archive-date=February 26, 2009|df=}}</ref> while storylines are produced on WWE's weekly television shows, ''[[Monday Night Raw]]'' and ''[[Friday Night SmackDown]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|title=WWE's 'Smackdown' Will Move To Live Broadcast On USA (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Steinberg|first=Brian|date=May 25, 2016|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=May 25, 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526113045/http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|archive-date=May 26, 2016|df=}}</ref>\n\nQualifying matches for the women's [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] began on the April 13 episode of ''Raw''. [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]], [[Shayna Baszler]], and [[Nia Jax]] qualified for the match by defeating [[Ruby Riott]], [[Sarah Logan]], and [[Kairi Sane]], respectively.<ref name=\"Raw04132020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=4/13 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s live review of Drew McIntyre and Becky Lynch appearances, Money in the Bank qualifying matches featuring Asuka vs. Ruby Riott, Kairi Sane vs. Nia Jax, and Sarah Logan vs. Shayna Baszler|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/13/4-13-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-of-drew-mcintyre-and-becky-lynch-appearances-money-in-the-bank-qualifying-matches-featuring-asuka-vs-ruby-riott-kairi-sane-vs-nia-jax-and-sarah-logan-v/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref> On the April 17 ''SmackDown'', [[Dana Brooke]] and [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]] will also compete for a spot in the women's match, while [[Cesaro (wrestler)|Cesaro]] and [[Daniel Bryan]] will compete in a spot for the men's match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/article/daniel-bryan-cesaro-money-in-the-bank-qualifying|title=Daniel Bryan to face Cesaro in Men\u2019s Money in the Bank Qualifying Match|website=WWE|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Matches ==\n<!-- Please do not add any matches you may have heard on the internet or during taping, without a reliable source, such as the company's official website or other reliable websites. -->\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|times  = \n|future = yes\n|match1 = [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]] vs. [[Shayna Baszler]] vs. [[Nia Jax]] vs. [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]] or [[Dana Brooke]] vs. [[TBD]] vs. TBD\n|stip1  = [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] for a [[Professional wrestling championship#Gender championships|women's championship]] match contract<ref>{{cite web|title=Women's Money in the Bank Ladder Match|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/moneyinthebank/2020/womens-money-in-the-bank-ladder-match|work=WWE|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref> \n|time1  = \n|match2 = [[Buddy Murphy]] vs. [[Aleister Black]]  vs. [[Apollo Crews]] vs. [[Daniel Bryan]] vs. [[Jeff Hardy]] vs. [[Sheamus]] \n\n|stip2  = [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] for a [[Professional wrestling championship#World championships|world championship]] match contract \n|time2  = \n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.wwe.com/shows/moneyinthebank|Money in the Bank Official Website}}\n\n{{2020 WWE Network events}}\n{{WWEPPV|Money in the Bank}}\n\n[[Category:2020 WWE Network events]]\n[[Category:2020 WWE pay-per-view events]]\n[[Category:WWE Money in the Bank|2020]]\n[[Category:May 2020 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Scheduled professional wrestling shows]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network event}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n<!--{{current sport|sport=pro wrestling|event=professional wrestling PPV}}-->\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name       = Money in the Bank (2020)\n|image      = \n|caption    = \n|tagline    = <!-- DO NOT PUT ANYTHING HERE WITHOUT A REFERENCE INCLUDED TO A WP:RS -->\n|promotion  = [[WWE]]\n|brand      = [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]]<br>[[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]\n|date       = May 10, 2020\n|attendance = <!-- DO NOT PUT ANYTHING HERE WITHOUT A REFERENCE INCLUDED TO A WP:RS -->\n|venue      = \n|city       = \n|wwenlast   = [[WrestleMania 36]]\n|wwennext   = \n|event      = [[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Money in the Bank (2019)|2019]]\n|nextevent2 = \n}}\n'''Money in the Bank''' is an upcoming [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] (PPV) and [[WWE Network]] [[List of WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network events|event]], produced by [[WWE]] for their [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brand divisions]]. It is scheduled to take place on May 10, 2020. It will be the eleventh event under the [[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]] chronology.\n\nThe event was originally scheduled to take place at the [[Royal Farms Arena]] in [[Baltimore, Maryland]], but the venue canceled all shows [[impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports|due to the]] [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. WWE has yet to announce changes in plans for the event.\n\n== Production ==\n=== Background ===\n[[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]] (MITB) is an annual [[Gimmick (professional wrestling)|gimmick]] pay-per-view produced by [[WWE]] since 2010 and generally held between May and July. The concept of the show comes from WWE's established [[Money in the Bank ladder match]], in which multiple wrestlers use [[Ladder match|ladders]] to retrieve a briefcase hanging above the ring. The briefcase contains a contract that guarantees the winner a match for a world championship of their choosing at any time within the next year. Both the men's and women's matches feature eight wrestlers, evenly divided between the [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brands]]. Male wrestlers compete for a contract to grant them a match for either Raw's [[WWE Championship]] or SmackDown's [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]], while female wrestlers compete for a [[Raw Women's Championship]] or [[SmackDown Women's Championship]] match contract. 2020 will be the eleventh event in the Money in the Bank chronology.<ref name=\"2020event\"/>\n\n====Impact of the coronavirus pandemic====\nThe event was originally announced with [[Baltimore]]'s [[Royal Farms Arena]] as host.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lambert|first=Jeremy|title=WWE Money In The Bank 2020 Scheduled For May 10 In Baltimore, MD|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/wwe-money-bank-2020-scheduled-may-10-baltimore-md|work=Fightful|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"2020event\">{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE MONEY IN THE BANK 2020 DETAILS|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/134349/wwe-money-in-the-bank-2020-details.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> However, [[Maryland]] issued a [[stay at home order]] on March 30, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Barnes|first=Sophia|url=https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/maryland-governor-larry-hogan-latest-monday-march-30-coronavirus-outbreak-covid-19-stay-at-home-order/2258161/|title=Maryland to Enact Stay-at-Home Order Monday as Coronavirus Cases Top 1,400|work=NBC4 Washington|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> Subsequently on April 9, the host venue cancelled the event due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], and began issuing refunds. WWE has yet to announce whether the event will still go on from a different location (such as the [[WWE Performance Center]] in [[Orlando]] where all of their other shows have been held since mid-March).<ref>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE MONEY IN THE BANK WILL NOT TAKE PLACE IN BALTIMORE, ROYAL FARMS ARENA ANNOUNCES CANCELLATION|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/135465/wwe-money-in-the-bank-will-not-take-place-in-baltimore-royal-farms-arena-announces-cancellation.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wilen|first=Jerome|title=WWE Money in the Bank pay-per view canceled due to COVID-19 outbreak|url=https://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/153495-wwe-money-in-the-bank-pay-per-view-canceled-covid-19/|work=WrestleView|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> WWE did air an advertisement promoting Money in the Bank during the second half of [[WrestleMania 36]], but with no references to a specific venue.<ref name=\"WM36Part2\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 results: Powell\u2019s live review of Night Two featuring Brock Lesnar vs. Drew McIntyre for the WWE Championship, John Cena vs. \u201cThe Fiend\u201d Bray Wyatt in a Firefly Funhouse match, Edge vs. Randy Orton in a Last Man Standing match, Rhea Ripley vs. Charlotte Flair for the NXT Women\u2019s Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/05/wrestlemania-36-results-powells-live-review-of-night-two-featuring-brock-lesnar-vs-drew-mcintyre-for-the-wwe-championship-john-cena-vs-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-in-a-firefly-funhouse-match/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Storylines===\nThe show will include matches that result from scripted storylines, where wrestlers portray [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] in scripted events that build tension and culminate in a wrestling match or series of matches. Results are predetermined by WWE's writers on the Raw and SmackDown brands,<ref name=\"HSW\">{{cite web|title=How Pro Wrestling Works|url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|last=Grabianowski|first=Ed|work=HowStuffWorks|publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]|access-date=March 5, 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|archive-date=November 18, 2013|df=}}</ref><ref name=WWEnt>{{cite web|title=Live & Televised Entertainment|url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|publisher=WWE|access-date=March 21, 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5esskNFVE?url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|archive-date=February 26, 2009|df=}}</ref> while storylines are produced on WWE's weekly television shows, ''[[Monday Night Raw]]'' and ''[[Friday Night SmackDown]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|title=WWE's 'Smackdown' Will Move To Live Broadcast On USA (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Steinberg|first=Brian|date=May 25, 2016|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=May 25, 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526113045/http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|archive-date=May 26, 2016|df=}}</ref>\n\nQualifying matches for the women's [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] began on the April 13 episode of ''Raw''. [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]], [[Shayna Baszler]], and [[Nia Jax]] qualified for the match by defeating [[Ruby Riott]], [[Sarah Logan]], and [[Kairi Sane]], respectively.<ref name=\"Raw04132020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=4/13 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s live review of Drew McIntyre and Becky Lynch appearances, Money in the Bank qualifying matches featuring Asuka vs. Ruby Riott, Kairi Sane vs. Nia Jax, and Sarah Logan vs. Shayna Baszler|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/13/4-13-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-of-drew-mcintyre-and-becky-lynch-appearances-money-in-the-bank-qualifying-matches-featuring-asuka-vs-ruby-riott-kairi-sane-vs-nia-jax-and-sarah-logan-v/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref> On the April 17 ''SmackDown'', [[Dana Brooke]] and [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]] will also compete for a spot in the women's match, while [[Cesaro (wrestler)|Cesaro]] and [[Daniel Bryan]] will compete in a spot for the men's match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/article/daniel-bryan-cesaro-money-in-the-bank-qualifying|title=Daniel Bryan to face Cesaro in Men\u2019s Money in the Bank Qualifying Match|website=WWE|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Matches ==\n<!-- Please do not add any matches you may have heard on the internet or during taping, without a reliable source, such as the company's official website or other reliable websites. -->\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|times  = \n|future = yes\n|match1 = [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]] vs. [[Shayna Baszler]] vs. [[Nia Jax]] vs. [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]] or [[Dana Brooke]] vs. [[TBD]] vs. TBD\n|stip1  = [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] for a [[Professional wrestling championship#Gender championships|women's championship]] match contract<ref>{{cite web|title=Women's Money in the Bank Ladder Match|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/moneyinthebank/2020/womens-money-in-the-bank-ladder-match|work=WWE|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref> \n|time1  = \n|match2 = [[Buddy Murphy]] vs. [[Aleister Black]]  vs. [[Ap